
[1]sledding

   SLED'DING, ppr. Conveying on a sled.

   SLED'DING, n. The act of transporting on a sled.

   2. The means of conveying on sleds; snow sufficient for the running of
   sleds. Thus we say in America, when there is snow sufficient to run a
   sled, it is good sledding during the winter.
